{Speech 2}{}{Stanwell's my name. You want to know something about caravans?}
{Speech 2 Answer 4}{}{Yes. What kind of caravan do you run?}
{Speech 2 Answer 5}{}{On what day does your caravan leave?}
{Speech 2 Answer 9}{}{Need a guard? I'd like to sign up.}
{Speech 2 Answer 10}{}{Need a guard? I'd like to sign up.}
{Speech 2 Answer 3}{}{No, I just happened to be passing by.}
{Speech 3}{}{Then get lost, I've got a lot to do.}
{Speech 4}{}{I run a caravan between the New California Republic and Redding. We always need extra guards. We leave town on the 11th of every month. If you want to come with us, show up here on that day.}
{Speech 4 Answer 6}{}{What time on the eleventh?}
{Speech 4 Answer 8}{}{And what do you haul?}
{Speech 4 Answer 7}{}{What's the pay?}
{Speech 4 Answer 9}{}{Need a guard, you say? I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 4 Answer 10}{}{Need a guard, you say? I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 4 Answer Exit}{}{Got it, that's all.}
{Speech 5}{}{On the 11th of every month. We go to NCR and back. If you want to come with us, you can find me here in the morning, same spot.}
{Speech 5 Answer 6}{}{What time on the eleventh?}
{Speech 5 Answer 8}{}{And what do you haul?}
{Speech 5 Answer 7}{}{What's the pay?}
{Speech 5 Answer 9}{}{Need a guard, you say? I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 5 Answer 10}{}{Need a guard, you say? I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{Got it, that's all.}
{Speech 6}{}{We set out at exactly 8 in the morning, so be here by around seven. We won't wait around for anyone, so we don't end up trudging under the sun. That way we'll make camp right around noon.}
{Speech 6 Answer 8}{}{What are we hauling?}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{Okay, and how much do you pay?}
{Speech 6 Answer 9}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 6 Answer 10}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 6 Answer Exit}{}{Got it, that's all.}
{Speech 7}{}{4000 bucks when we get there. But don't think it'll be easy money. We go right through Death Valley, if that means anything to you. Same again if you decide to come back with us.}
{Speech 7 Answer 8}{}{What are we hauling?}
{Speech 7 Answer 9}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 7 Answer 10}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{Got it, that's all.}
{Speech 8}{}{Gold, obviously. What else can you get out of this backwater hole? On the way back we drive brahmin.}
{Speech 8 Answer 7}{}{Okay, and how much do you pay?}
{Speech 8 Answer 9}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 8 Answer 10}{}{I'm ready to go with you.}
{Speech 8 Answer Exit}{}{Got it, that's all.}
{Speech 9}{}{Great, we need guys with balls.}
{Speech 9 Answer 12}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{Alright, I'll come back when it's time.}
{Speech 10}{}{Great, we need guys with bal... Hey, you sure you can handle this?}
{Speech 10 Answer 11}{}{Maybe I don't have balls of my own, but I shoot at other folks' just fine.}
{Speech 10 Answer 11*}{}{I'll manage, don't worry. At the very least I can run around and jab stimpaks into people.}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{I'll have to think about it. I'll come back when I've grown some balls.}
{Speech 11}{}{Okay... Then listen up.}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{[Next]}
{Speech 12}{}{Come here on the morning of the 11th. We set out at 8, I'll be waiting here from seven. We don't wait for latecomers.}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{No problem, Stanwell. I'll be back on the 11th at 7.}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit*}{}{I'm not sure@sex@||| I'll really go, but if I make up my mind I'll come.}
{Speech 13}{}{We're not ready to set out yet. Come on the 11th at 7.}
{Speech 14}{}{Any minute now. Stay close, or we might think you decided not to go.}
{Speech 15}{}{Hurry up! If you don't make it before eight, you'll be stuck in this dump.}
{Speech 16}{}{There's this pre-war movie... Sold once on a holodisk for crazy cash. Once upon a time there was a pretty girl with skin even whiter than yours, like she'd spent her whole life in a Vault... She wandered around, then stumbled into a cave where seven big black men lived, even blacker than me. And she decided to stay and live with them.}
{Speech 16 Answer 17}{}{And what happened next?}
{Speech 17}{}{Well, what do you think seven big men could get up to with one pretty little girl? Heh-heh-heh.}
{Speech 20}{}{Boo.@@Get out of here.@@Don't annoy me.}
{Speech 95}{}{Hey, Snow White, ready@sex@||| to hit the road?}
{Speech 95 Answer 14}{}{Yes, when do we leave?}
{Speech 95 Answer 15}{}{Wait, I've got something to finish.}
{Speech 95 Answer 16}{}{Snow... who?}
{Speech 95 Answer Exit}{}{I don't think I'll be guarding the caravan this time.}
{Speech 98}{}{So, shall we move?@@Seems quiet enough. Ready@sex@||| to ride?@@Shall we push on? I've got this feeling a dozen centaurs are about to come running out from behind a rock.@@My gut tells me we shouldn't linger here. Ready@sex@||| to ride?@@We can keep moving. Ready@sex@|||?}
{Speech 98 Answer Exit}{}{Yeah, let's go.@@Let's move!@@On the road!@@Yeah, I can't wait to get out of here.}
{Speech 98 Answer Exit*}{}{Hold on, let me tie my shoelace.@@One second, I need the toilet.@@Wait, let me see if there's anything worth picking up here.@@Hold on, I need to rest a couple of minutes.}
{Speech 100}{}{Didn't expect@sex@||| to see me, huh?! @sex@|Bastard||}
{Speech 101}{}{Hey, aren't you @sex@|the asshole|the bitch| who ditched@sex@||| the caravan right in the middle of the road last time?}
{Speech 101 Answer 115}{}{Stanwell, sorry, I got really scared@sex@|||. But I want to guard caravans again!}
{Speech 101 Answer 114}{}{What?! I told@sex@||| you I needed to step away @sex@|to take a piss|to make pee-pee|, and you wandered off somewhere, left me in the middle of the Wasteland, you idiots.}
{Speech 101 Answer Exit}{}{Uh... You weren't supposed to see me! Bye!}
{Speech 102}{}{How have you decided@sex@||| to ruin this nice sunny day this time?@@Get lost, I don't want anything to do with you anymore.@@Buzz off, you're not even worth wasting bullets on.@@Come around here one more time and I'll send you straight to the hubologist gods.}
{Speech 103}{}{Oh! @pname@, if I'm not mistaken? Glad to see you again. You acted@sex@||| bravely back then, but sorry, we couldn't save you. You still with us?}
{Speech 103 Answer 12}{}{Yes, I still want to guard caravans.}
{Speech 103 Answer 111}{}{No, I've got no desire to do that anymore. I just wanted@sex@||| to check on you.}
{Speech 104}{}{Didn't expect to see me? Ha! The hubologists work miracles. I'm back on my feet and running caravans again. You still want to go with us?}
{Speech 104 Answer 12}{}{Yes.}
{Speech 104 Answer 111}{}{No.}
{Speech 105}{}{Here's your pay. We'll be standing here for four hours, then we head back to Redding. You coming with us?}
{Speech 105 Answer 110}{}{Yes, wait for me. There's nothing to do in this brahmin pen.}
{Speech 105 Answer 111}{}{No, I've got things to do here.}
{Speech 106}{}{Here's your money. Great work, @sex@|son|sweetie|. [Winks] If you want to come with us again, come back on the eleventh. As for me, I need to rest and screw my wife.}
{Speech 106 Answer Exit}{}{Good luck, Stanwell. Be safe. [Wink]}
{Speech 106 Answer Exit*}{}{Unless I get killed first...}
{Speech 106 Answer Exit**}{}{Like hell I'll do this again for that kind of money.}
{Speech 110}{}{Great, while there's time you can drop your money in the bank and stock up on ammo at Buster's. I'll go have some iguana in the meantime.}
{Speech 110 Answer Exit}{}{[Exit]}
{Speech 111}{}{If you change your mind, come back.}
{Speech 112}{}{So, changed your mind@sex@|||?}
{Speech 112 Answer 113}{}{Yes, I'm with you.}
{Speech 112 Answer Exit}{}{No, I just happened to be passing by.}
{Speech 113}{}{Stay close, we leave soon.}
{Speech 114}{}{Hmm... [Thinks it over] Yeah, maybe there was something like that. Fine. You still want to work with us?}
{Speech 114 Answer 12}{}{Yes.}
{Speech 114 Answer Exit}{}{Yes.}
{Speech 115}{}{Go to hell, I don't want anything to do with you anymore.}
